\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 3. The "So What" Connectors\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Between each layer, the dashboard should include brief explainer text that connects cause to effect. These are the most important part for public understanding:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Global 
\f6 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Regional
\f1\b0 : "Australia doesn't refine most of its own fuel. When crude prices spike or shipping routes are disrupted, it directly affects the refineries in South Korea and Singapore that produce the petrol and diesel we import."\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Regional 
\f6 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Domestic
\f1\b0 : "About 90% of Australia's petrol and diesel arrives as already-refined product on tanker ships from Asia. A typical shipment takes 1-3 weeks to arrive. If Asian refineries cut output or prioritise their own markets, our stocks start falling."\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Domestic 
\f6 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Retail
\f1\b0 : "Australia's 'days of supply' figure measures how long our fuel stocks would last at normal consumption rates. But panic buying can spike demand by 50%+, which means those 38 days of petrol supply effectively shrink. Meanwhile, distribution bottlenecks mean some regional areas run dry even when national stocks look adequate."\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

